SIMPLE: scutibranchiata
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scutibranchiata
<hw>Scu`ti*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Scutum</er>, and <er>Branchia</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of gastropod Mollusca having a heart
with two auricles and one ventricle. The shell may be either spiral or
shieldlike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It is now usually regarded as including only the
Rhipidoglossa and the Docoglossa. When originally established, it
included a heterogenous group of mollusks having shieldlike shells, such
as Haliotis, Fissurella, Carinaria, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scutibranchiate</ent>⟦br⟧
